@node User Specified TYPENAME Keyword
@subsubsection User-Specified TYPENAME keyword

@quotation Note
The @code{TYPENAME} keyword is part of the original SDL language format.  This
particular implementation foes not currently support either the Ada or PL/I
languages.  As a result, this keyword is parsed but ignored in the current
implementation.
@end quotation
@cindex User specified names
@cindex TYPENAME keyword

The @code{TYPENAME} keyword is used to specify a data type name that is not an
OpenSDL data type.  Depending on which back end is specified, this name may or
may not override the OpenSDL data type.  The Ada and PL/I back ends use these
data type names as parameter data types, as return value data types, and as
@code{CONSTANT} declaration data types.
@cindex CONSTANT declaration
@cindex Data type, TYPENAME
@cindex TYPENAME keyword

The @code{TYPENAME} keyword has the following syntax:

@example
TYPENAME name
@end example
@cindex TYPENAME example

The Ada language translation (as a result of processing the OpenSDL source file
@file{/usr/lib/OpenSDL/example/example.sdl}) shows an example of the
@code{TYPENAME} keyword.  The following is an example of the @code{TYPENAME}
keyword on each of the parameters in an @code{ENTRY} declaration:

@example
ENTRY SYS$FAO
    ALIAS $FAO
    PARAMETER (CHARACTER REFERENCE NAMED CTRSTR IN TYPENAME CHARDESC,
        WORD UNSIGNED NAMED OUTLEN OUT DEFAULT 0 TYPENAME NUMBER,
        CHARACTER REFERENCE NAMED OUTBUF OUT TYPENAME CHARDESC,
        LONGWORD VALUE NAMED P1 OPTIONAL LIST TYPENAME VARIES)
    RETURNS LONGWORD TYPENAME CONDVALU;
@end example
