@node BITFIELD Data Type
@subsubsection BITFIELD Data Type
The @code{BITFIELD} keyword specifies a bit field variable that must be a
member of an @code{AGGREGATE} declaration.  The @code{BITFIELD} data type has
the following syntax:
@cindex AGGREGATE keyword
@cindex AGGREGATE declaration
@cindex AGGREGATE member
@cindex BITFIELD keyword
@cindex BITFIELD declaration
@cindex BITFIELD data type
@cindex Data type, BITFIELD

@example
BITFIELD [LENGTH n] [MASK] [SIGNED] [RADIX x];
@end example

@strong{@code{[LENGTH n]}}
@indentedblock
Is any valid OpenSDL expression giving the number of bits in the bitfield.  If
no length is specified, OpenSDL uses a default length of 1 bit.
@end indentedblock
@cindex BITFIELD declaration
@cindex LENGTH declaration

@strong{@code{[MASK]}}
@indentedblock
Is a keyword specifying that OpenSDL generate both a bitfield variable and a
constant bit mask representing the bits defined in this field.
@end indentedblock
@cindex BITFIELD declaration
@cindex MASK keyword

@strong{@code{[SIGNED]}}
@indentedblock
Is a keyword specifying that OpenSDL treat the output as a signed field.
@end indentedblock

@strong{@code{[RADIX x]}}
@indentedblock
Is a keyword where 'x' is one of @code{DEC}, @code{OCT}, or @code{HEX}.
@end indentedblock

Bitfields must be @code{AGGREGATE} declaration members.  They cannot be scalar
items, objects of @code{ADDRESS} declarations, parameters, or return data types
of entries.  The following is an example of the @code{BITFIELD} keyword used in
an @code{AGGREGATE} declaration that specifies a structure with two bitfield
members:
@cindex AGGREGATE keyword
@cindex AGGREGATE declaration
@cindex AGGREGATE member
@cindex BITFIELD keyword
@cindex BITFIELD data type
@cindex BITFIELD declaration
@cindex Data type, BITFIELD
@cindex Scalar items

@example
AGGREGATE flags STRUCTURE PREFIX tst_;
    resolved BITFIELD MASK SIGNED;
    spare_bits BITFIELD LENGTH 5;
END;
@end example
@cindex AGGREGATE example
@cindex BITFIELD example
@cindex END keyword
@cindex LENGTH example
@cindex MASK example
@cindex PREFIX example

The declaration of resolved in the previous example results in two declarations
in the output file: a declaration for the bitfield itself and a declaration of
a constant mask whose value is 1.  Because the @code{PREFIX} option is
specified for this aggregate, the source output file identifiers produced for
this declaration are @code{tst_v_resolved} and @code{tst_m_resolved}, where the
tag @code{v_} indicates the bitfield variable and the tag @code{m_} indicates
the mask.  Prefixes and tags are described in more detail in
@ref{PREFIX MARKER and TAG Keywords}.
@cindex Identifiers, OpenSDL generated
@cindex PREFIX keyword
@cindex TAG keyword

@subsubsection BOOLEAN Data Type

The @code{BOOLEAN} keyword specifies a Boolean data type that is a one-byte
field that can have one of two values, 0 or 1.  The @code{BOOLEAN} data type
