@node CHARACTER Data Type
@subsubsection CHARACTER Data Type
@cindex CHARACTER declarations
@cindex Data type, CHARACTER

The @code{CHARACTER} keyword declares a character string of a given length.
The @code{CHARACTER} data type has the following syntax:

@example
CHARACTER [LENGTH @{n@}] [VARYING]
          [       @{*@}]
@end example

@strong{@code{[LENGTH n]}}
@indentedblock
Is the length of the character string.  The length can be specified using any
valid OpenSDL expression.  If no length is specified, OpenSDL uses a default
length of 1 character.  You can specify a character string of unknown length
using @code{LENGTH *}.  An unknown length character string can be specified
only for parameter types.  For example:
@cindex LENGTH declaration

@example
ENTRY LIB$ROUTINE PARAMETER(CHARACTER LENGTH * NAMED foo);
@end example
@end indentedblock
@cindex CHARACTER example
@cindex ENTRY example
@cindex LENGTH example
