@cindex CHARACTER example
@cindex CONSTANT example
@cindex DIMENSION example
@cindex END keyword
@cindex EQUALS example
@cindex LENGTH example
@cindex PREFIX example

In the previous example, the local symbol @code{#opsize} captures the byte
offset following the fixed length portion of the structure operator.  This
value is subsequently used in the @code{CONSTANT} declaration, which defines
the size of the constant portion of the structure in words.  The @code{flags}
structure is byte aligned by the field @code{filler}, which makes use of the
current bit offset symbol to compute the size of this field.  The
@code{CONSTANT inst_size} defines the size of the entire structure.
