@section ENTRY Description

An @code{ENTRY} declaration produces an external procedure or function
declaration in the output file.  You must specify a valid entry name on the
@code{ENTRY} declaration.  You may also specify any or all of the @code{ENTRY}
declaration options described in @ref{Keywords Used in Declarations} in
@ref{Declaration Modifier Keywords} and shown within the context of an
@code{ENTRY} declaration in @ref{ENTRY Format}.

The following example shows the @code{ENTRY} declaration for the OpenVMS system
service @code{SYS$GETJPI}:

@example
ENTRY SYS$GETJPI ALIAS $GETJPI PARAMETER (
    LONGWORD UNSIGNED VALUE NAMED EFN DEFAULT 0 TYPENAME EFNUM,
    LONGWORD UNSIGNED NAMED PIDADR IN OUT DEFAULT 0 TYPENAME PROCID,
    CHARACTER REFERENCE NAMED PRCNAM IN DEFAULT 0 TYPENAME PROCNAME,
    ANY NAMED ITMLST IN TYPENAME ITEMLIST,
    QUADWORD UNSIGNED NAMED IOSB OUT DEFAULT 0 TYPENAME IOSB,
    ADDRESS(ENTRY) NAMED ASTADR DEFAULT 0 TYPENAME ASTADR,
    LONGWORD UNSIGNED VALUE NAMED ASTPRM DEFAULT 0 TYPENAME USERPARM
    ) RETURNS LONGWORD TYPENAME CONDVALU;
@end example
